Gov. Willie Obiano of Anambra, has sympathised with the family of a woman and her child burnt to death in a truck accident in Onitsha, the commercial city of the  state.<img class="size-full wp-image-1273381 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=640%2C320&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="320" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=300%2C150&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=768%2C384&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=1024%2C512&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=58%2C29&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=260%2C130&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=200%2C100&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?resize=560%2C280&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/truck-fire.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> It would be recalled that the tanker had an accident and spilled its product which subsequently caused the fire outbreak. Reacting to the fire accident at the Ochanja market, the second biggest market in Onitsha, Obiano directed owners of properties affected by the tragic accident, including shop owners, to report at the Conference Room of the Secretary to the State Government on Monday, Oct. 21, 2019. Anambra community sues govt N4.75bn for destroying 4 shrines, 3 deities(Opens in a new browser tab) He said the meeting would enable the state government know how to assist them. Obiano who spoke in a statement issued by the Commissioner for Information and Public Enlightenment Don Adinuba said that a panel would be set up immediately to determine the cause of the accident. Adinuba also said the panel would ascertain why the firemen could not put out the fire and how the condition of the victims can be ameliorated. Obiano prayed for the repose of the souls of the woman and child who died in the accident, adding that the Anambra State Government would assist their families in their burials. Vanguard Watch the video of the raging fire below:  Tales of woes and lamentations, yesterday, continued to trail the Onitsha tanker fire incident that razed a filling station, 10 vehicles, 13 buildings and other properties worth millions of naira on Upper New Market Road in Onitsha. February 17, 2017 In "News" Gov. Willie Obiano of Anambra on Thursday ordered the relocation of filling stations constructed around residential buildings and markets February 16, 2017 In "News" Many people were trapped and feared dead, yesterday, while scores of persons sustained injuries in Onitsha, Anambra State, as a petrol-laden tanker lost control, crashed into Toronto Hospital at Upper Iweka, along Enugu-Onitsha Expressway and burst into flames. October 17, 2019 In "News"